	   <a name=97979698627984></a>
	   <form action=http://www1.allakhazam.com/perl/strategy/mrate.pl name=f97979698627984><tr><td id=headerrow><a id=sj href=classes.html?class=6&mid=97979698627984>New Pally Spells!</a> <a id=fs8 href=classes.html?class=6&mid=97979698627984#post><img src=http://everquest.allakhazam.com/static/reply.gif border=0 alt="Reply..." height=16 width=16></a></td><td align=right id=headerrow valign=bottom><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=21267><span id= >Durim</span></a>, <span id= > </span><br><span id=notbold>3 posts</td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Thu, Jan 18th 5:52 AM 2001</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Decent<span id=notbold>[3.00]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>some funny stuff i ran across on the official eq board. thought it would be appropriate if i reposted here (i dont think it's been posted here, but i could be wrong. apologies if i am)<br><br><a href="http://boards.station.sony.com/everquest/Forum2/HTML/049265.html" target=_new>http://boards.station.sony.com/everquest/Forum2/HTML/049265.html</a><br><br>posted 01-17-2001 08:32 PM&nbsp;&nbsp;          <br>--------------------------------------------------<br><br>This post is from a paladin board that I follow, I did not compose this myself. I just thought it was funny and wanted to share it.<br>Apparently weve been too hard on Verant, this latest release details the mysterious new spells referred to in the patch message. And we thought Verant wasn&#8217;t listening to our concerns. A complete revamp of all 51+ spells<br><br>Paladin&#8217;s spells added: <br><br>50th level, Summon Oreo: This summons one Oreo Cookie. This gives you something to eat while you sit in the corner out of your groups way. After all, you're just there to fill up a slot while your group takes full advantage of the new exp system <br><br>51st level, Summon Milk: This is to complement the level 50 spell. <br><br>52nd level, Yellow Streak of Ro: This spell makes you invisible so you can enjoy your cookies and milk in peace. <br><br>53rd level, Summon Group Particles: This spell makes it appear as if you are casting a awesome group buff. Many spectacular particles will encompass your group though nothing really happens. It is recommended that you have Particles turned on High for maximum effect. <br><br>54th level, Steely Glare: This was actually planned to be a discipline but was thought to be far to over balancing. Steely Glare is a paladin only emote that allows you to impress the opposite sex with your dominating presence. It should be noted that Verant is considering giving this spell to druids, necros and shaman as well so as to keep these classes equally useful in high-level groups. <br><br>55th level, Boast: This will automatically send messages to the targeted player/mob proclaiming the exploits of the Paladin. If no target is selected the spell becomes an AoE and effects everything within /tell range. <br>Example: <br><br>Zalhava begins to cast a spell.<br><br>Zalhava tells you, I once killed a_orc_centurian_011 in East Commons. <br><br>This can either be used to again impress other players, or as a taunt on NPC's. <br><br>56th level, Group True North: This is perhaps the most useful spell in the game. <br><br>57th level, Tunare's Holy Gleaming: Self-only flavor buff: This spell will cause any equipped shield or weapon to gleam and pulse as if it were a true instrument worthy of a paladin. This however is its only effect. (Quest only)<br><br>58th level, Shroud of Bertoxx: This summons a death shroud with which a paladin can cover his corpse; thereby by masking it from other players. This is meant to help the paladin retain a good reputation amongst his peers and prevent those embarrassing "Nekkid Paladin" pictures your guild keeps collecting. <br><br>59th level, Pacification of the Merchants: This is an AoE agro reduction spell much like Harmony. However it only affects friendly, non-aggressive merchants.<br><br>60th level, Holy Sundering: This spell is an awesome DD spell. Doing 548 pts of damage for 150 mana it is the most mana efficient spell in the game. However it can only be cast upon Orc Pawns. This may sound like a nerf however it is still GREAT for impressing newbies in East Commons.<br><br><br>&nbsp;<br>Durim Brightblade<br>Paladin of Marr, 20th Circle<br>Prexus</td></tr>
