	   <tr><td colspan=2>Ah, I remember fondly the days of reckless youth! Running through the Commonlands, hunting 'wisps for their glowing orbs, always wary for lumbering hill giants...<br><br>...but I digress. You should never buy yourself a magic weapon. A true paladin must always earn his blade. I would suggest that you embark on the quest for the Shining Star of Light. I quested for that item (with a friend) back when I was around the 11th circle or so, and it turned out to be well worth it. The quest is not too grueling and you end up with a nice magic weapon that you can use well into the high teens. Plus, it will force you to work on your 1-handed blunt skill (which you've probably been neglecting).<br><br>Talk to Astaed Wemore, in the Temple of Life at Queynos to begin thy quest. Best of luck, noble Paladin! May Marr be with you.<br><br>&nbsp;<br>Durim Brightblade<br>Paladin of Marr, 20th Circle<br>Prexus</td></tr>
