	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Thu, Jan 18th 5:27 AM 2001</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Excellent<span id=notbold>[4.55]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>The zones I have seen the most auctions are the N. Freeport (bank), E. Commons (tunnel), and G. Faydark (Kelathin Bank).&nbsp;&nbsp;These 3 places have people loitering around doing nothing but selling stuff.  Everywhere else I've seen auctions haven't been consistent auctioning zones.  I've bought things, on occasion, by just hearing a good auction while running through a zone.  Try advertising that you wish to buy an axe of the iron back, blackened iron bastord sword, a polished granite tomahawk, or a practice sword.  I think you are bit too old for a mino axe.  The practice sword is a bit more expensive than the other items I listed.  Those others will run from 100 to 200 pp... even less if the seller has been trying to sell it for a while.  If they ask you what your offer is, say 50 pp and see how they haggle with you.  =)  If they offer a price to you, split it in half.  Ack, anyways.. I'm trying to tell you how to haggle, and that's not my business.  You'll find a good magic weapon, worry not.  =)<br><br>Souldragoon Flamingheart<br>40th circle Paladin of Virtue<br>Fennin Ro<br>&nbsp;<br><i>Follow virtue, and the virtuous will follow you.</i></td></tr>
