	   <tr><td colspan=2>This probably doesnt answer your question but maybe it'll make you feel better. A couple of days ago I was camping the Mucktail gnolls in High Hold with a cleric and a bard. The ledge is a small area and another group came over to sit right beside us to compete with us. In the spirit of comradism I asked them NICELY to leave coz we had been sitting there for the past 3 hours. They wouldnt budge though. The leader's reason was that there is no such thing as a camp and its a free world. I agree to that point and told him its only manners and respect to fellow players that one should have. Well he didnt get the point and challenged me with his Lvl 28 Paladin (he was playing a bard then). I told him to shoot off and that his Paladin has no honor (which he agreed). I wanted no conflict and hostility so I got my group to leave the ledge and let them have the whole thing. <br><br>Not 10 mins later the Mucktail popped and the other group jumped on him and got nearly got him down, but Captain Orben came along and decided to rid High Hold of another nasty Mucktail. BANG WHANG. Captain Orben killed the Mucktail and they didnt get the loot. One of the group member shouted Capt Orben KS their kill and I shouted " GRATZ"<br><br>After that the leader sent me a tell saying I was a crybaby and I was afraid to die by camping easy gnolls. I told him I fight where I wanted and his comments doesnt bother me coz it sounded like it came from a child.<br><br>It didnt bother me that the Mucktail popped after we left, coz I was having a great time with the cleric and the bard and anyways I have CDS already.<br><br>What I'm saying is act with honor and integrity like a true Paladin and maybe, just maybe, EQ world in its wierd and corky way would take care of retribution for you.<br><br>Paladin of the 23rd Campaign<br>( No names and server are mentioned coz I'm not trying to flame someone )<br><br><br>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
