	   <tr><td colspan=2>I'm new to the game and my character is a level 10 Ranger. I've read the post about Rangers vs Pallys on both this board and the Rangers. I have a question, what is the difference between AC and HP for these 2 classes at high levels and also compared to the Warrior? My friend has let me play his Lvl 54 Ranger a bit and he seems to rock. He has 1700 HP self-buffed, an AC of 822 and an attack rating of 971. Also has Firestrike, a DD spell causing 302 damage. He wields a Revultant whip and Flux Bladed Axe (procs a 150 DD spell). His AC comes from a full set of TV except chest, where he has Treeweave. Never played a high level Pally so would be interested to know his capabilities.<br><br>I also think that Rangers are a good soloing class but I do think they can be an asset to a group. Firstly, they can do a lot of damage with dual wield and double attack and the main tank should be able to taunt the MOB off you right? Secondly, they have useful utility spells (esp. SOW even if others have it). Thirdly, they can act as a back-up healer/caster while your main healer/caster needs to Med. Also, we are master trackers. I'm talking in theory rather than experience so feel free to correct me if I'm wrong. <br><br>I guess you'll reply that a Lvl 54 Pally will have 3000 HP's, an AC of 1200 and an attack rating of 900? :-)<br>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
