	   <tr><td colspan=2>Well, you sorta had the right idea on the response.&nbsp;&nbsp;=)  Yes, pallies will have whole heck of alot more hp and AC at higher levels.  Rangers do deal out more damage with their duel wield, but cannot take as much punishment as a pally.  It's the price of being a bit more on the wizard side.  Rangers are an offensive asset as long as they aren't the primary 'tank'.  A warrior is by far prefered for taking all the tanking blows, but pallies (and I guess are darker cousins...) come right up after them in defense.  A tanking pally and a ranger assisting with the damage is a good pairing to make up for a missing warrior tank.  =)  Exp gets split up more, but hey, I have to form some sort of defense for pallies joining groups.  My advice to you is to not worry which class you play.  You are new now, but in a few months you won't be new anymore.  Your character will have advanced a great deal, and you may even decide to start other characters.  By the time you are a veteran, you'll probably have a few high level characters.  Just have fun while you play, and make sure others are having fun because of you.  That's all that matters.<br><br>Souldragoon Flamingheart<br>40th circle Paladin of Virtue<br>Fennin Ro<br>&nbsp;<br><i>Follow virtue, and the virtuous will follow you.</i></td></tr>
