	   <tr><td colspan=2>I should just save a word document on my computer and cut/paste responses to this ever popular question!&nbsp;&nbsp;=)  If it's exp AND loot you're after, then just look at this page I already made up.  <a href=HTTP://www.geocities.com/kingsofbrotherhood/members/Souldragoon/sashes.htm target="_new" target=_new>Bandit sashes.</a>  If you ever drop by South Karana, you will find it to be one of the most popular places for persons of your level range to hunt, though not as much loot as the bandits.  On that note, it can get CROWDED!  Personally, I grouped for orcs in the oasis until I was 18, then went to Unrest, with a little temple of cazic thule in there, until I was 32.  The lake of ill omen is becoming popular for people at and around level 20.  I think big, expansive zones are the most sought after hunting grounds.  You don't feel cramped there, and you don't feel trapped.  Trains are easier to avoid, too.  Whatever tickles yer pleasure, I suppose!  =)  Just remember to HAVE FUN wherever you go!<br><br>Souldragoon Flamingheart<br>40th circle Paladin of Virtue<br>Fennin Ro<br>&nbsp;<br><i>Follow virtue, and the virtuous will follow you.</i></td></tr>
